ept des Bandes, anhand von Leitfragen die einzelnen Positionen miteinander in Beziehung zu bringen, ist konsequent auf die Bedürfnisse eines strukturierten BA-Studiums zugeschnitten.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aSocial sciencesvPhilosophy. 4aEinführung. 4aGesellschaft. 4aSozialität. 4aSozialphilosophie. 4aSoziologie. 4aSoziologische Theorie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aIntroduction.  aSocial Philosophy.  aSocial Relations.  aSociety.  aSociology.1 aDimbath, Oliver, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMaurer, Andrea, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPelizäus, Helga, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSchmid, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2010-2013z9783110352856oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Sozialw. 2010-2013z9783110370713oZDB-23-TSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2013z9783110401219oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.978383941708940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839417089423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839417089/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-TGPb2013  aZDB-23-TSOc2010d2013  aZDB-23-TSWc2010d2013